{{see|muppet}}
==English==

===Etymology===
{{wikipedia}}
Possibly a [[blend]] of '''[[marionette]]''' and '''[[puppet]]''', a Muppet being operated partly like a [[glove puppet]] and partly like a marionette

===Proper noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A type of puppet popularised by ''[[w:Sesame Street|Sesame Street]]'' and ''[[w:The Muppet Show|The Muppet Show]]'', typically operated with one hand of the [[puppeteer]] inside the head and a rod to move one arm of the puppet.

